  "verdict": "PROCESS-GENERAL UNDER CROSSING. The BAM Compton vertex factor F\u00b2(x, c) = 4\u00b7x\u00b3\u00b7(x\u00b2+1\u2212x\u00b7sin\u00b2\u03b8)/[(1+c\u00b2)(1+x)\u00b2], when expressed in Lorentz-invariant form and analytically continued via standard Mandelstam crossing (s_C \u2192 u_BW, t_C \u2192 s_BW, u_C \u2192 t_BW), exactly reproduces the Breit-Wheeler differential and total cross sections. The Compton-side construction is not a process-specific algebraic fit \u2014 it is the closed form of the invariant QED amplitude in Compton variables, and crossing carries it to BW automatically. The same closed-form F (with x_\u2297 < 0 as the analytic continuation of \u03c9\u2032/\u03c9) governs pair production."
